%% Diagram: Redlock clock-jump failure — quorum split-brain via skewed expiry
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C1 as Client 1
    participant A as Redis A
    participant B as Redis B
    participant C as Redis C
    participant D as Redis D
    participant E as Redis E
    participant C2 as Client 2

    Note over A,E: TTL = 30 s on every instance
    C1->>A: SET NX PX 30000
    A-->>C1: OK
    C1->>B: SET NX PX 30000
    B-->>C1: OK
    C1->>C: SET NX PX 30000
    C-->>C1: OK
    Note over D,E: D, E unreachable
    Note over C1: Quorum (A,B,C) — lock held

    Note over C: Wall clock on C jumps +25 s (NTP step)
    Note over C: C expires the key early

    C2->>C: SET NX PX 30000
    C-->>C2: OK
    C2->>D: SET NX PX 30000
    D-->>C2: OK
    C2->>E: SET NX PX 30000
    E-->>C2: OK
    Note over C2: Quorum (C,D,E) — also "holds" lock

    Note over C1,C2: Split-brain — both quora overlap on C
